00:12:28,639 --> 00:12:30,360
They haven't had this tea ever since.

296
00:12:30,679 --> 00:12:31,799
I've never tried it either.

297
00:12:31,919 --> 00:12:32,759
Try it out.

298
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,200
It should taste good.

299
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,639
She says it's a great tea.

300
00:12:35,919 --> 00:12:37,320
She's kept them for a long time.

301
00:12:37,519 --> 00:12:38,639
-Okay.
-Enjoy yourself.

302
00:12:38,879 --> 00:12:39,919
Okay.

303
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:43,480
How many lawyers are working in this firm?

304
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,679
How many lawyers do you have?

305
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:46,600
Three.

306
00:12:46,919 --> 00:12:47,519
Three.

307
00:12:47,759 --> 00:12:48,279
No,

308
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,120
there are four.

309
00:12:49,519 --> 00:12:50,559
Four.

310
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,360
Are you also

311
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,120
a lawyer?

312
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,480
Are you a lawyer too?

313
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:56,840
I'm not.

314
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,120
I'm just a receptionist.

315
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,440
I am also the janitor.

316
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,559
But the lawyers and I

317
00:13:02,559 --> 00:13:04,399
work as a team.

318
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:05,799
I alone

319
00:13:06,159 --> 00:13:07,720
can handle several jobs.

320
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,879
She says she's tough enough

321
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:12,080
to do a lot of work at the same time.

322
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:13,960
Do you think

323
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,360
we can entrust

324
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:18,159
our legal affairs to such a firm?

325
00:13:21,679 --> 00:13:22,320
What did he say?

326
00:13:23,399 --> 00:13:24,000
Nothing.

327
00:13:24,759 --> 00:13:25,679
It's just that...

328
00:13:27,159 --> 00:13:27,399
He...

329
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:28,600
Is it because

330
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,639
our law firm is too small for him?

331
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:31,960
It's not that.

332
00:13:32,679 --> 00:13:33,519
Please, tell him

333
00:13:34,039 --> 00:13:34,799
that our small firm

334
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,320
is capable of great things.

335
00:13:37,759 --> 00:13:39,600
The God of Wealth is a minor god,

336
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:42,039
but every family worships the deity.

337
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:44,840
What is she saying?

338
00:13:45,399 --> 00:13:46,759
She's from the countryside.

339
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:49,039
She just kept on telling the local stories.

340
00:13:49,279 --> 00:13:51,000
I don't understand why this company

341
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,200
asks a peasant woman to welcome us.

342
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,840
Did they hire you to be the receptionist?

343
00:13:58,159 --> 00:13:59,000
No.

344
00:13:59,519 --> 00:14:00,919
I asked for the job myself.

345
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:04,399
She insisted herself
on being the receptionist here.

346
00:14:04,679 --> 00:14:05,679
Wait, what?

347
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,320
I live in a rural village.

348
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:10,159
I had some disputes with the villagers,

349
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,200
so I moved into the city.

350
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:14,039
So, I started working here.

351
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:18,919
They pay me

352
00:14:18,919 --> 00:14:20,440
1,500 yuan a month.

353
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,600
What? Only 1,500 yuan?

354
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:25,679
That's a very low salary.

355
00:14:26,679 --> 00:14:28,080
Even you agree it's too low.

356
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:29,879
I think so too.

357
00:14:30,039 --> 00:14:32,080
I've asked for a raise.

358
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:36,159
She keeps asking them to increase her salary.

359
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:39,440
So, why are you still working here?

360
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,480
Why do you still work here?

361
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,320
Because they are good people.

362
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:45,200
They are...

363
00:14:46,919 --> 00:14:48,000
They are...

364
00:14:50,559 --> 00:14:52,639
They treat everyone equally.

365
00:14:54,559 --> 00:14:55,799
They never look down on me

366
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:57,080
simply because

367
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,399
I came from a rural village.

368
00:14:59,120 --> 00:14:59,639
She says

369
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,879
they are good men with integrity,

370
00:15:02,159 --> 00:15:03,720
that they never look down on her

371
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,679
though she's from the countryside.

372
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,320
And then, I became their receptionist.

373
00:15:08,559 --> 00:15:10,080
They also gave me a raise.

374
00:15:10,639 --> 00:15:13,440
Finally, they end up
increasing her salary for her.

375
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,679
Okay, not bad.

376
00:15:15,879 --> 00:15:16,639
Not bad?

377
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:18,240
Not bad.

378
00:15:18,559 --> 00:15:20,720
Not bad indeed.

379
00:15:25,679 --> 00:15:26,720
We won the lawsuit.

380
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:27,720
Ladies and gentlemen!

381
00:15:28,559 --> 00:15:29,759
What you must do now

382
00:15:29,759 --> 00:15:31,279
is to leave your signatures here.

383
00:15:31,279 --> 00:15:31,919
Then,

384
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:33,279
leave your thumbprints

385
00:15:33,399 --> 00:15:34,600
above your names.

386
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:36,360
-Sure!
-Okay!

387
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,240
One at a time.

388
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:38,720
Thank you, Mr. Guan.

389
00:15:38,799 --> 00:15:40,399
You're welcome to have dinner at our home.

390
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,519
-Thank you so much.
-Thank you so much.

391
00:15:42,519 --> 00:15:43,360
Let's have dinner at my place!

392
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:44,720
Don't mention it.

393
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:45,320
You deserve this.

394
00:15:45,759 --> 00:15:46,559
You're welcome at our home.

395
00:15:47,159 --> 00:15:48,159
We really need to thank you.

396
00:15:50,519 --> 00:15:51,879
Hey, Xingfu!

397
00:15:51,879 --> 00:15:53,360
Why are you calling me?

398
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,399
How did it go over there?

399
00:15:56,039 --> 00:15:56,759
The hearing is over.

400
00:15:57,879 --> 00:15:58,600
And?

401
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,360
And everything ends well.

402
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:01,279
I told you

403
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:02,679
I wouldn't leave them behind!

404
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:03,960
Don't worry,

405
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,399
everyone is satisfied with the result.

406
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:07,720
They are inviting me to their homes for dinner.

407
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,320
Come to my house.

408
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:09,080
Forget about the dinner,

409
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,039
come back now!

410
00:16:10,759 --> 00:16:11,480
What is it?

411
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,320
Is it something urgent?

412
00:16:12,559 --> 00:16:14,039
Fra...

413
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,120
It's Frank.

414
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,320
Mr. Frank is here.

415
00:16:17,159 --> 00:16:19,159
Okay.

416
00:16:19,159 --> 00:16:21,150
Mr. Guan. Please stay.

417
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:22,060
How long has he been there?

418
00:16:22,110 --> 00:16:22,900
What does he need?

419
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:24,060
He's been here for a while.

420
00:16:24,060 --> 00:16:25,230
We had a chat.

421
00:16:25,780 --> 00:16:27,540
I think they want to work with you.

422
00:16:28,390 --> 00:16:29,350
Just come back now.

423
00:16:29,350 --> 00:16:30,820
I ran out of things to talk about.

424
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,030
Why didn't you say so earlier?

425
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:32,940
You should have told me sooner.

426
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:34,820
I was worried...

427
00:16:35,110 --> 00:16:36,350
I didn't want

428
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:39,300
to distract you from the lawsuit.

429
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:41,580
Don't be silly.

430
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:43,180
Look,

431
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,230
use whatever means you have

432
00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:46,940
to keep Frank at our office.

433
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:47,940
I'll be right back.

434
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:52,180
Grab our stuff,

435
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:53,110
we're heading back.

436
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:55,750
[Circuit Court of Xiuchuan County People's Court]
Mr. Guan, stay!

437
00:16:55,870 --> 00:16:56,700
Another day, perhaps.

438
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:57,660
-We need to go now.
-Mr. Guan.

439
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:00,780
Chinese culture

440
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,580
values fateful encounters.

441
00:17:03,420 --> 00:17:04,620
It's a big world.

442
00:17:05,230 --> 00:17:06,430
We meet

443
00:17:06,580 --> 00:17:07,990
and work with each other

444
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:09,670
because of fate.

445
00:17:10,950 --> 00:17:11,860
I often think

446
00:17:11,860 --> 00:17:14,140
Mr. Guan and his friends
and I are brought together by fate.

447
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,430
Look,

448
00:17:15,430 --> 00:17:16,750
they are all well-educated people

449
00:17:17,470 --> 00:17:18,470
with great degrees.

450
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:20,430
I didn't even finish middle school.

451
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:23,430
But how did I meet them?

452
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,950
Why would they let me be on their team?

453
00:17:27,340 --> 00:17:28,750
That must be fate.

454
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:30,710
Mr. Frank,

455
00:17:31,230 --> 00:17:33,060
you've only met each other once,

456
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:35,780
but you are willing to come here for them.

457
00:17:36,580 --> 00:17:38,060
And now, we meet.

458
00:17:38,710 --> 00:17:39,990
This must be fate!

459
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:41,910
She's talking something about fate.

460
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:44,190
The fate between Mr. Guan and her.

461
00:17:44,990 --> 00:17:46,060
And she asks you

462
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:47,580
if you think

463
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:50,140
it's also fate that you've come all the way here

464
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:51,510
to meet Mr. Guan.

465
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,540
Even though you've just met him once.

466
00:17:56,380 --> 00:17:57,990
What do you mean about fate?

467
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:00,340
What is fate to you?

468
00:18:01,190 --> 00:18:02,580
Fate is...

469
00:18:04,510 --> 00:18:05,540
It's...

470
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:09,300
Imagine there was a crowd of people.

471
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:11,300
When I looked over,

472
00:18:12,580 --> 00:18:13,270
you'd be right there.

473
00:18:15,470 --> 00:18:18,620
It's something like you pick out someone

474
00:18:19,030 --> 00:18:21,670
among a bunch of people
at the first sight of him.

475
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:29,140
What happened to the other lawyers?
Why are they not back yet?

476
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,620
Why are they not back yet?

477
00:18:31,910 --> 00:18:33,060
They went to a village

478
00:18:33,190 --> 00:18:34,780
to help the villagers with a lawsuit.

479
00:18:35,140 --> 00:18:37,140
It's tough helping out the villagers.

480
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:39,710
There are all kinds of requests from them.

481
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:42,060
Most of them don't understand the law.

482
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:45,030
But Mr. Guan and his friends
still take their requests very seriously.

483
00:18:45,340 --> 00:18:46,910
They can't abandon

484
00:18:46,910 --> 00:18:48,190
the villagers who are in need.

485
00:18:48,780 --> 00:18:50,580
That's why they often go to the villages.

486
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:52,430
Oh, really?

487
00:18:53,950 --> 00:18:57,510
Is it really possible to make money
by defending peasants in a lawsuit?

488
00:18:58,430 --> 00:18:59,340
Do they make much money

489
00:18:59,340 --> 00:19:00,100
by helping villagers

490
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,030
in lawsuits?

491
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:02,580
Of course,

492
00:19:03,030 --> 00:19:04,430
it's not a very lucrative job.

493
00:19:05,030 --> 00:19:06,860
That's why we can only afford
this rundown office.

494
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:07,780
But

495
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:08,950
just as Mr. Guan once said,

496
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:10,270
a lawyer

497
00:19:10,470 --> 00:19:13,430
must serve the people with the law.

498
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:16,380
A lawyer mustn't simply use the law
as a means to make money.

499
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:19,190
Mr. Guan said

500
00:19:19,510 --> 00:19:21,580
that they'd use the law to serve the people

501
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:23,380
and they don't just take it as a business.

502
00:19:24,510 --> 00:19:25,380
Okay.

503
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:27,990
Well, I think he's quite good.

504
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:32,990
-Okay?
-Yes.

505
00:19:32,990 --> 00:19:33,750
Congratulations.

506
00:19:35,620 --> 00:19:37,140
Guan, what is going on now?

507
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:39,060
Frank came to visit our firm.

508
00:19:39,060 --> 00:19:40,580
Xingfu has been keeping him there.

509
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:45,030
Frank came?

510
00:19:45,030 --> 00:19:46,430
Why didn't she tell us sooner?

511
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:49,030
Use your brilliant brain and think.

512
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:52,540
I get it now.

513
00:19:52,990 --> 00:19:53,710
Wait,

514
00:19:53,820 --> 00:19:55,300
Xingfu must be so full of herself.

515
00:19:55,990 --> 00:19:57,860
She received Frank on her own
just so we could finish

516
00:19:57,860 --> 00:19:59,030
the lawsuit in the village?

517
00:19:59,430 --> 00:20:00,300
Guan Tao, listen.

518
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:01,710
If Frank leaves,

519
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:02,620
fire her immediately.

520
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:04,580
Enough talking. Just drive.

521
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:06,270
I can't imagine the mess she's made.

522
00:20:17,746 --> 00:20:18,875
[Fangyuan Law Firm]

523
00:20:30,780 --> 00:20:31,510
It seems fine.

524
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:33,860
Xingfu managed to keep him here.

525
00:20:45,060 --> 00:20:45,950
Are you guys ready?

526
00:20:57,580 --> 00:20:58,140
Sigh.

527
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:04,380
I told you so.

528
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:06,190
There is no way he would want

529
00:21:06,190 --> 00:21:07,580
to hire a small firm like ours.

530
00:21:10,430 --> 00:21:11,140
Xingfu,

531
00:21:12,030 --> 00:21:12,580
where's Frank?

532
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:13,910
He left.

533
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:14,620
He left?

534
00:21:15,060 --> 00:21:15,860
Didn't you ask him to stay?

535
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:17,100
I tried,

536
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,060
but he still left.

537
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:19,670
He insisted on leaving.

538
00:21:20,710 --> 00:21:22,750
I made him a wonderful pot of tea,

539
00:21:23,230 --> 00:21:24,950
and he only took a small sip.

540
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:29,950
Oh, no.

541
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:32,710
What's wrong?

542
00:21:32,710 --> 00:21:34,340
Didn't you win the lawsuit?

543
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:35,230
Forget it.

544
00:21:35,230 --> 00:21:36,860
I stayed up all night,

545
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:39,950
I'm beat. I need a nap.

546
00:21:40,710 --> 00:21:41,470
Wait.

547
00:21:41,620 --> 00:21:42,620
Who should I hand this to?

548
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:44,140
Frank left his business card.

549
00:21:44,340 --> 00:21:45,820
He wants you to contact him.

550
00:21:51,860 --> 00:21:52,540
Guan Tao.

551
00:22:00,710 --> 00:22:01,670
Shameless jerks!

552
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:03,380
Shameless jerks!

553
00:22:03,670 --> 00:22:04,230
Shameless jerks!

554
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:04,910
Those foreigners

555
00:22:04,910 --> 00:22:06,820
should be ashamed of themselves!

556
00:22:06,820 --> 00:22:07,780
He's never been so furious.

557
00:22:07,780 --> 00:22:09,910
Why should we work for them
if they are not paying?

558
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:12,820
Mr. Han.

559
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:15,580
They want to terminate the contract.

560
00:22:16,020 --> 00:22:17,150
Fine, so be it.

561
00:22:18,260 --> 00:22:19,430
That is a breach of contract.

562
00:22:19,430 --> 00:22:20,740
They must pay us a year's worth of counsel fees.

563
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:21,630
Let them terminate the contract.

564
00:22:21,630 --> 00:22:22,500
But Mr. Han,

565
00:22:22,870 --> 00:22:24,740
they have the proof that we instigated them

566
00:22:24,740 --> 00:22:26,340
to bribe the officials.

567
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:28,580
Fine.

568
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:30,390
They can show the proof if they want.

569
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:32,300
Let's see who'll have the last laugh!

570
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:44,630
Well?

571
00:22:44,630 --> 00:22:45,150
What?

572
00:22:45,150 --> 00:22:45,950
Did you close the deal?

573
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:46,630
What deal?

574
00:22:46,630 --> 00:22:48,060
Did you come here just for a chat?

575
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:48,740
Yeah.

576
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:50,340
Without a proper chat, I wouldn't have gotten this.

577
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:52,820
What do we have here?

578
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:55,300
What is this?

579
00:22:58,670 --> 00:22:59,470
It's been signed!

580
00:22:59,470 --> 00:23:00,580
You closed the deal, Guan Tao!

581
00:23:00,710 --> 00:23:01,780
That's 3,000,000 yuan!

582
00:23:05,780 --> 00:23:07,020
Am I dreaming or something?

